objects.name: Lingerie and Swimsuit
objects.description: Shops offering lingerie, undergarments and swimwear that utilize images of semi-nude models for the purpose of selling or promoting such items. Such websites do not intend to sexually arouse.

objects.name: Religion
objects.description: Global religions such as Buddhism, Bahai, Christianity, Christian Science, Hinduism, Islam, Judaism, Mormonism, Shinto, and Sikhism, as well as atheism. These sites also cover related activities, events, and resources, including those for religious organizations, leaders, places of worship, and religious items.

objects.name: Torrents and Peer-to-peer
objects.description: Bittorrent links aggregators that allow users to share files between each other.

objects.name: Science and Technology
objects.description: Science materials, information technology, technology in general, technical information, artificial intelligence.

objects.name: Message Boards and Forums
objects.description: Online discussion spaces, such as bulletin boards and independent forums, where users can exchange messages and engage in conversations.

objects.name: Command and Control
objects.description: Resources that host command-and-control (C2) URLs and domains. These are used by malware or compromised systems to secretly communicate with an attacker's remote server, enabling the receipt of malicious instructions or the unauthorized extraction of data.
